QueryText: ASKING FOR COCONUT RHINOCEROS BEETLE CONTROL
KccAns: Management:i Cultural Method:Remove and burn all dead coconut trees in the garden which are likely to serve as breeding ground to maintain good sanitationCollect and destroy the various bio-stages of the beetle from the manure pits breeding ground of the pest whenever manure is lifted from the pitsii Mechanical Method:During peak period of population build up the adult beetle may be extracted from the palm crown using GI hooksSet up light traps following the first rains in summer and monsoon period to attract and kill the adult beetlesiii Chemical Method:The topmost three leaf axils around the spindle may be filled with any of the following mixtures as a prophylactic measure:a Sevidol 8G 25 g  fine sand 200 g which is to be done thrice in a year in April-May September-October and December-January b For seedlings apply Naphthalene balls 105 g approx three to four balls covered with fine sand once in 45 daysPlace phorate 10 G 5 g in perforated sachets in two inner most leaf axils for 2 times at 6 months intervalsTreat manure pits and other possible breeding sites with 001 carbaryl 50  WP on ww basis Treatment will have to be repeated every six monthsiv Trap Method:

QueryText: Management of rhinoceros beetle
KccAns: Recommended to provide field sanitation to prevent breeding of beetles Hook out the beetle from the attacked palms using beetle hook As a prophylactic measure application of 250 gram neem cake or marotti  cake mixed with equal volume of sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils This treatment is to be done twice ie during April-May before the onset of south-west monsoon and during September-October after the south-west monsoonNaphthalene balls 120 gram approx 4 nos can be put in the innermost 2 leaf axils adjacent to spindle leaf and covered with fine sand once in 45 daysSpray Metarrhizium anisopliae 250 ml Metarrizhium culture  750 ml water in manure pits and other breeding sites of the beetle Incorporation of Clerodendron infortunatum  10  ww basis in the cowdung and manure pitsCrown cleaning followed by the application of 20 gram Fipronil mixed with 200 gram sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils The application has to be done thrice during January May and September

QueryText: Coconut Rhinoceros beetle management
KccAns: Management:i Cultural Method:Remove and burn all dead coconut trees in the garden which are likely to serve as breeding ground to maintain good sanitationCollect and destroy the various bio-stages of the beetle from the manure pits breeding ground of the pest whenever manure is lifted from the pitsii Mechanical Method:During peak period of population build up the adult beetle may be extracted from the palm crown using GI hooksSet up light traps following the first rains in summer and monsoon period to attract and kill the adult beetlesiii Chemical Method:The topmost three leaf axils around the spindle may be filled with any of the following mixtures as a prophylactic measure:a Sevidol 8G 25 g  fine sand 200 g which is to be done thrice in a year in April-May September-October and December-Januaryb For seedlings apply Naphthalene balls 105 g approx three to four balls covered with fine sand once in 45 days

QueryText: Asked about management of Rhinoceros Beetle in coconut
KccAns: Recommended to clean the crown and apply 20 gram Cartap hydrochloride 4 G mixed with 200 gram sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils The application has to be done thrice during January May and SeptemberSpray Metarrhizium anisopliae 250 ml Metarrizhium culture 750 ml water in manure pits and other breeding sites of the beetle

QueryText: Asked about management of rhinoceros beetle in coconut
KccAns: Recommended to provide field sanitation to prevent breeding of beetles Hook out the beetle from the attacked palms using beetle hook As a prophylactic measure application of 250 gram neem cake mixed with equal volume of sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils This treatment is to be done twice ie during April-May before the onset of south-west monsoon and during September-October after the south-west monsoonNaphthalene balls 120 gram approx 4 nos can be put in the innermost 2 leaf axils adjacent to spindle leaf and covered with fine sand once in 45 daysSpray Metarrhizium anisopliae 250 ml Metarrizhium culture  750 ml water in manure pits and other breeding sites of the beetle Incorporation of Clerodendron infortunatum  10  ww basis in the cowdung and manure pitsSet pheromone traps outside the plantation Crown cleaning followed by the application of 20 gram Cartap hydrochloride 4 G or Fipronil 03 G mixed with 200 gram sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils The application has to be done thrice during January May and SeptemberRhinoceros beetle attack may predispose palms to bud rot infection So clean the crown and spray Bordeaux mixture 1 on the crown of the palms as a prophylactic measure or pouring Mancozeb solution 5 gram 300 ml of water coupled with placing of small perforated sachets 2 no containing 3-4 gram Mancozeb 75 WP in the inner most leaf axils is found to be effective

QueryText: Asked about management of rhinoceros beetle in coconut
KccAns: Recommended to provide field sanitation to prevent breeding of beetles  As a prophylactic measure application of 250 gram neem cake mixed with equal volume of sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils This treatment is to be done twice ie during April-May before the onset of south-west monsoon and during September-October after the south-west monsoon Naphthalene balls 120 gram approx 4 nos can be put in the innermost 2 leaf axils adjacent to spindle leaf and covered with fine sand once in 45 days

QueryText: Asked about management of rhinoceros beetle in coconut
KccAns: Recommended to provide field sanitation to prevent breeding of beetles Hook out the beetle from the attacked palms using beetle hook As a prophylactic measure application of 250 gram neem cake mixed with equal volume of sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils This treatment is to be done twice ie during April-May before the onset of south-west monsoon and during September-October after the south-west monsoonNaphthalene balls 120 gram approx 4 nos can be put in the innermost 2 leaf axils adjacent to spindle leaf and covered with fine sand once in 45 daysSpray Metarrhizium anisopliae 250 ml Metarrizhium culture  750 ml water in manure pits and other breeding sites of the beetle Incorporation of Clerodendron infortunatum  10  ww basis in the cowdung and manure pitsSet pheromone traps outside the plantation Crown cleaning followed by the application of 20 gram Chlorantraniliprole 04G Ferterra mixed with 200 gram sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils The application has to be done thrice during January May and September

QueryText: Asked about management of Rhinoceros beetle in coconut
KccAns: Recommended to provide field sanitation to prevent breeding of beetles Hook out the beetle from the attacked palms using beetle hook As a prophylactic measure application of 250 gram neem cake mixed with equal volume of sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils This treatment is to be done twice ie during April-May before the onset of south-west monsoon and during September-October after the south-west monsoonNaphthalene balls 120 gram approx 4 nos can be put in the innermost 2 leaf axils adjacent to spindle leaf and covered with fine sand once in 45 daysSpray Metarrhizium anisopliae 250 ml Metarrizhium culture  750 ml water in manure pits and other breeding sites of the beetle Incorporation of Clerodendron infortunatum  10  ww basis in the cowdung and manure pitsSet pheromone traps outside the plantation Crown cleaning followed by the application of 20 gram Chlorantraniliprole 04G Ferterra mixed with 200 gram sand in the innermost 2-3 leaf axils The application has to be done thrice during January May and SeptemberRhinoceros beetle attack may predispose palms to bud rot infection So clean the crown and spray Bordeaux mixture 1 on the crown of the palms as a prophylactic measure or pouring Mancozeb solution 5 gram 300 ml of water coupled with placing of small perforated sachets 2 no containing 3-4 gram Mancozeb 75 WP in the inner most leaf axils is found to be effective

QueryText: COCONUT Rhinoceros beetle CONTROL MANAGEMENT
KccAns: Apply mixture of either neem seed powder  sand 1:2 150 g per palm or neem seed kernel powder  sand 1:2 150 g per palm in the base of the 3 inner most leaves in the crownSoak castor cake at 1 kg in 5 liter of water in small mud pots and keep them in the coconut gardens to attract and kill the adults

QueryText: COCONUT Rhinoceros beetle:CONTROL MANAGEMENT
KccAns: Management:i Cultural Method:Remove and burn all dead coconut trees in the garden which are likely to serve as breeding ground to maintain good sanitationCollect and destroy the various bio-stages of the beetle from the manure pits breeding ground of the pest whenever manure is lifted from the pitsii Mechanical Method:During peak period of population build up the adult beetle may be extracted from the palm crown using GI hooksSet up light traps following the first rains in summer and monsoon period to attract and kill the adult beetlesiii Chemical Method:The topmost three leaf axils around the spindle may be filled with any of the following mixtures as a prophylactic measure:a Sevidol 8G 25 g  fine sand 200 g which is to be done thrice in a year in April-May September-October and December-Januaryb For seedlings apply Naphthalene balls 105 g approx three to four balls covered with fine sand once in 45 daysPlace phorate 10 G 5 g in perforated sachets in two inner most leaf axils for 2 times at 6 months intervalsTreat manure pits and other possible breeding sites with 001 carbaryl 50  WP on ww basis Treatment will have to be repeated every six monthsSet up Rhino lure pheromone trap  5 trapsha to trap and kill the beetles The dispenser may be hanged in a plastic bucket having 2 liter of insecticide solution once in a week Trapped beetles can be disposed offv Biological Method:Application of green muscardine fungus Metarrhizium anisopliae  5 x 1011 spores  m3 - spray 250ml Metarrizhium culture  750ml water in manure pits to check the perpetuation of the pestField release of Baculovirus oryctes inoculated adult rhinoceros beetle  15 beetlesha reduces the leaf and crown damage caused by this beetleSoak castor cake at 1 kg in 5 liter of water in small mud pots and keep them in the coconut gardens to attract and kill the adultsApply mixture of either neem seed powder  sand 1:2 150 g per palm or neem seed kernel powder  sand 1:2 150 g per palm in the base of the 3 inner most leaves in the crown

QueryText: Asked about control measures for Rhinoceros beetle: Oryctes rhinoceros in coconut
KccAns: Control measures for Rhinoceros beetle: Oryctes rhinoceros in coconut: Management:i Cultural Method:Remove and burn all dead coconut trees in the garden which are likely to serve as breeding ground to maintain good sanitationCollect and destroy the various bio-stages of the beetle from the manure pits breeding ground of the pest whenever manure is lifted from the pitsii Mechanical Method:During peak period of population build up the adult beetle may be extracted from the palm crown using GI hooksSet up light traps following the first rains in summer and monsoon period to attract and kill the adult beetlesiii Chemical Method:The topmost three leaf axils around the spindle may be filled with any of the following mixtures as a prophylactic measure:a Sevidol 8G 25 g  fine sand 200 g which is to be done thrice in a year in April-May September-October and December-Januaryb For seedlings apply Naphthalene balls 105 g approx three to four balls covered with fine sand once in 45 daysPlace phorate 10 G 5 g in perforated sachets in two inner most leaf axils for 2 times at 6 months intervalsTreat manure pits and other possible breeding sites with 001 carbaryl 50  WP on ww basis Treatment will have to be repeated every six monthsiv Trap Method:Rhinoceros BeetleTrapped Rhinoceros BeetleSet up Rhino lure pheromone trap  5 trapsha to trap and kill the beetles The dispenser may be hanged in a plastic bucket having 2 liter of insecticide solution once in a week Trapped beetles can be disposed off
